      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0647P0-02589'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0647P0_20030410_GCR_252' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Baroness said: The amendment is designed to probe where the Government have got to with regard to their stated commitment to find ways in which to increase access to water for sport and informal recreation. That commitment was restated in <span class="italic">Directing the Flow</span> in November 2002. I am sure that the Minister and the noble Baroness, Lady Farrington, remember our debate during the passage of the <a href="/acts/countryside-and-rights-of-way-act-2000">Countryside and Rights of Way Act</a> on that issue. That is why my noble friend Lord Mar and Kellie attached his name to the amendment. Along with us, he has continued to be concerned about what is happening in this context.
